'''VRChat Feedback''' (or "Canny" - the software's name) is an official website - available at ''{{VRC link|https://feedback.vrchat.com|feedback.vrchat.com}}'' - used to gather community feedback to influence product decisions and help improve the platform. The feedback might include feature requests, bug reports and ideas for a multitude of supported platforms, websites and other VRChat initiatives.

Users might create posts with their feedback, comment on existing ones, or upvote them. The posts are categorized in boards, each dedicated to a specific platform, feature, release, software, initiative etc. VRChat developers might comment on and track selected posts, labelling them as e.g. "Interested", "In progress" or "Completed", depending on the platform's interests and progress.

=== Requirements ===
To create a post, comment, or upvote, user must log in with their VRChat account and have a [[Special:MyLanguage/Trust Rank|trust rank]] of "New User" or higher.

=== Boards ===

==== General ====

* '''Feature Requests''' - Requests for changes or additions to the VRChat platform.
* '''Bug Reports''' -  [[Reporting#Reporting a bug|Bugs]] on the VRChat platform.
* '''World/Udon Bugs & Feature Requests'''
* '''Avatar Bugs & Feature Requests'''
* '''SDK Bug & Feature Requests'''
* '''Localization''' - Localization issues.
* '''VRChat+ Feature Ideas''' - Suggesting new features for [[VRC+]].

==== Beta ====

* '''Open Beta''' - Feedback, feature requests, and bug reports for [[Open Beta]] builds and branches.
* '''Steam Audio Open Beta''' -  Feedback, feature requests, and bug reports for Steam Audio Open Beta.
* '''Android Limited Beta''' - Feedback, feature requests and bug reports for Android limited beta.
* '''iOS Closed Beta''' - Feedback, feature requests and bug reports for iOS closed beta.

